e {{USS|Triton|SSRN-586|6}} completes the [[Operation Sandblast|first submerged circumnavigation of the globe]]. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Robert Noyce]] is granted a [[patent]] for an [[integrated circuit]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Nguyen Hue Offensive]]: The [[North Vietnam]]ese 320th Division forces 5,000 [[South Vietnam]]ese troops to retreat and traps about 2,500 others northwest of [[Kontum]]. *[[1974]] &ndash; [[Carnation Revolution]]: A leftist military [[coup]] in Portugal overthrows the authoritarian-conservative ''[[Estado Novo (Portugal)|Estado Novo]]'' regime and establishes a democratic government. *[[1975]] &ndash; As [[People's Army of Vietnam|North Vietnamese forces]] close in on the [[South Vietnam]]ese capital [[Saigon]], the Australian Embassy is closed and evacuated, almost ten years to the day since the first Australian troop commitment to South Vietnam. *[[1981]] &ndash; More than 100 workers are exposed to radiation during repairs of at the [[Tsuruga Nuclear Power Plant]] in Japan. *[[1982]] &ndash; [[Israel]] completes its withdrawal from the [[Sinai Peninsula]] per the [[Camp David Accords]]. *[[1983]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: American schoolgirl [[Samantha Smith]] is invited to visit the [[Soviet Union]] by its leader [[Yuri Andropov]] after he read her letter in which she expressed fears about [[nuclear warfare|nuclear war]]. * 1983 &ndash; ''[[Pioneer 10]]'' travels beyond [[Pluto]]'s orbit. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Mswati III]] is crowned King of [[Swaziland]], succeeding his father [[Sobhuza II]]. *[[1988]] &ndash; In [[Israel]], [[John Demjanjuk]] is sentenced to death for [[war crime]]s committed in World War II. *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Violeta Chamorro]] takes office as the [[President of Nicaragua]], the first woman to hold the position. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Michele Alboreto]] is killed while testing an [[Audi R8 (race car)|Audi R8]] at the [[EuroSpeedway Lausitz|Lausitzring]] in Germany. *[[2004]] &ndash; The [[March for Women's Lives]]