{{ESC National Year | Year = 1994 | Country = Lithuania | Preselection = Internal selection | Entrant = [[Ovidijus Vyšniauskas]] | Song = [[Lopšinė mylimai]] | Final result = Last, 0 points | Next = 1999 }}
'''Lithuania''' participated in the '''Eurovision Song Contest 1994''' in [[Dublin]]. [[Ovidijus Vyšniauskas]] represented Lithuania with the song "[[Lopšinė mylimai]]". He finished in last place with 0 points.
==At Eurovision== Vyšniauskas performed 16th, following Slovakia's "Nekonečna Piesen" and preceding Norway's "Duett". He scored 0 points and Lithuania became the first ex-Soviet country which failed to score a single point. The Lithuanian jury gave its 12 points to runner up Poland. As of 2019, this is the only internally selected Lithuanian entry, as the next ones onward were chosen via national final.
